Summary Chapter 4
-Links are created using the <a> element
-The <a> element uses the href attribute to indicate the page you want to link to
-If you are linking to a page within your own site it is best to use relative links rather than absolute URLs
-You can create links to open email programs with an email address in the "mailto" field
-You can use the id attribute to target elements within a page that can be used to link the user